Christine Lillico was supposed to look after her elderly parents' bank accounts . 
  She stole almost £80,000 from John and Audrey Air over a six year period . 
  Mother-of-two was jailed for 20 months and ordered to pay her brother £39,000 . 
  Newcastle Crown Court heard she plundered their life savings to bankroll her own lifestyle . 
  John Air was left in debt and too poor to afford a telephone . 
  She was trusted with looking after their accounts as their health deteriorated . 
 